				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Most effective training for a Young Bard<a name="54413"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 30 04 9:49 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Soto, 
<br />
   You have a ton of options, I think the first thing you should do is take a look at the FAQ in the guide section, put together by Shass and contributed to by just about all of us. This might help give you some clear guidelines and answer some questions, after that check out the sections for your lvl and take a peek at what some other bards your age are asking about and hunting, etc. It's tough to give you solid direction at this point because there are a lot of areas you need to cover as you grow, but it's all part of being a bard. The more advanced tactics like swarming and chanting you won't have to worry about for a bit, but right now if you want some solo action take a look at AEing. 
<br />
</span></td>
