				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Most effective training for a Young Bard<a name="54436"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 30 04 11:22 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>At some point very soon, you will find it hard to tank.  You'll have more downtime and less exp coming in per session of play.  I have some wrist problems so its hard for me to kite day after day.  At level 42, I mix up my exping methods.  Some days I tank and others I charm kite.  I can 2-box, so I have a 65 druid standing behind me for heals.  I have found that charm kiting is the easiest method of kiting.  I don't have to keep my guy moving constantly.  Swarm kiting is probably the fastest form of exp so far.  The best place I found to learn charm or swarm kiting is in EW.  There's lots of room to learn the mechanics.  Good luck with your bard and hope I was able to help you a little bit =)</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
