				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Most effective training for a Young Bard<a name="54504"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 30 04 5:00 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Yeah, I do recommend the LDoNs as you level up, and besides, remember that the augments can make a huge difference.  I have a ton of charisma augments and a lot of others as well, plus the LDoN augment that goes inside your charm can end up with 10 to all stats, 10 to all resists and 100 HPS/100 mana.  So winning a LOT of LDoNs as you level up is great down the road.
<br />

<br />
Plus you learn all your grouping skills and also learn your songs as you get them.
<br />

<br />
Swarming and stuff levels you really really fast, but you only ever use a couple of songs.  I don't knock the bards that do it that way, I myself have chant kited for a little bit of AA xp every now and then, but I prefer grouping any day =)</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
