				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Most effective training for a Young Bard<a name="54524"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 30 04 7:23 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I rarely solo but I would suggest learning to swarm with your lvl 27 charm. 
<br />

<br />
I say this because of the &quot;on the fly&quot; mob cycling, don't let selo's drop, twist some chant experience it gives you. It really is a good exercise in how a bard operates differently from any other character. The charm only lasts 18 sec so it's great at keeping you on your toes. If you learn this you will be able to handle any of the other aspects of a bard fairly well.
<br />

<br />
Ldon can be good for this type of stuff also, but you are putting your group at risk while you learn things. Thats why I suggest learning the swarm kite first.</span></td>
