				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Most effective training for a Young Bard<a name="54818"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 2 04 4:44 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Be very very wary of impatient people, Soto. Do your thing and ignore them, your speed will increase in time. That was totally rude of that person to go around you and pull like that, every once in awhile you run into cocky fools like this who seem intent on getting everyone killed, just try to keep a cool head and do your thing, people will notice, they always do. Instead of pulling doubles and triples, try leaving the current mob when it's around 30-40% and going ahead to lull for the next pull, that way you can get a new single back to the group by the time the last one is dead. This is called chain-pulling and there are tons of variations on it using mezzes and charms and such. The most important thing about pulling is that you <u>Take Your Time!!</u>. Speed and rythm comes naturally through experience, eventually you'll have the timing pegged so that there is always a constant stream of singles, but if you rush things you only end up with adds and a mess on your hands, go for percision instead and you won't need to rush at all but the group will still have to try to keep up with you. 
<br />
Practice practice practice!!!
<br />
and don't let the impatient idiot jerk-offs get on your nerves, 90% of people out there are not like that and the others in your group will see them acting like a jerk and you handling it like an adult, so do your thing!
<br />
<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

<br />
-Edited to add this-
<br />
It may be debatable but I think Collect missions are the easiest and best to get good practice on chain pulling. The amount of time it takes is usually pretty short so there's plenty of room for some give and take, error-wise. Later on you can do slaughter and rescue and stuff, but I really reccommend sticking to collect while you are getting your feet wet. 
<br />
<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" /> </span></td>
