			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Most effective training for a Young Bard<a name="56936"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 16 04 1:42 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Thank you once again for all of the excellent advice.
<br />

<br />
The timing of my pulls is getting better, as I have taken to leaving once a MoB gets down to about 20% health.  As I keep a steady stream of singles, and a couple doubles (I always charm the add now, it really does rock), I have been fortunate enough to win all of the adventures I have been on.
<br />

<br />
I have befriended a Monk and a Ranger who have joined me on multiple adventures, but I am still having problems finding a regular healer.  Last night I tried a normal adventure without a healer and found that it went amazingly well.  Had a Paladin and the above mentioned Ranger doing what they could to heal, while adding DPS, and the Monk a Warrior and a Rogue also helped that DPS through the roof.
<br />

<br />
Is there any group that a bard cannot make work in a LDoN adventure at lower levels?
<br />

<br />
Funny thing was I had several people in these groups tell me it was their first win when we were done.  I thought that winning was a forgone conclusion.  Did have one close call, but that was due to a bad level disparity in the group that caused the MoBs to be red to alot of the group (including me) and using a Shaman as a healer and a Ranger as the tank.
<br />

<br />
Anyway thank you very much for all of your helpful advice.  The training offered on this site is the equivalent of Juliard to the performer.
<br />

<br />
P.S.  The audience has been very appreciative of my efforts too, I usually get several Bravo calls at the least, and mostly get requests for an Encore <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" /> </span></td>
